title: Ole Miss kicks off Oct. 17 against Memphis at 11 a.m.
text:
Ole Miss kicks off Oct. 17 against Memphis at 11 a.m. Daniel Paulling, The Clarion-Ledger 1:23 p.m. CDT October 5, 2015 Ole Miss will kick off against Memphis at 11 a.m. on Oct. 17. (Photo: Spruce Derden, Spruce Derden-USA TODAY Sports) 5 CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
OXFORD — Ole Miss will kick off its Oct. 17 road game against Memphis at 11 a.m. 
It will be the Rebels’ second consecutive 11 a.m. kick and third this season, joining the season opener against UT-Martin. The game will be the Rebels’ first appearance on ABC since Sept. 6, 2008, and the 32nd time in program history. 
The Rebels (4-1, 2-1 Southeastern Conference) is No. 13 in this week’s Amway Coaches Poll, while Memphis (5-0, 2-0 American Athletic Conference) is No. 25. The Rebels are 48-10-2 against Memphis, which includes last year's 24-3 home win. 
Ole Miss plays host to New Mexico State for homecoming Saturday at 11 a.m., while Memphis has a bye this weekend.
